column15: lively, shuffling and is sitting more upright now, still struggling and dragging himself a long to see the owner. Eating really well. still unable tos tand, discussion - euth, taken home for burial.

MELTING ULCER - PTS. OR noticed eye sore in the last few days, bathing with salty water but seems to be red, swollen and gunky today. <<name>> eating and drinking ok. R eye ok. L eye severe chemosis, pus discharge. Used proxymetacaine to anaesthetise to allow evaluation - ulcer 6x6mm and 1-2mm raised edges. Fl uptake on surface. Advised severe ulceration. High risk of rupture. Recommended emergency appt with opthalmologist, <<name>> to provide service. O not keen spending thousands to repair. Recommended enucleation, as can have good qol with one eye, again O not keen on spending a lot of money. Advised only other option is pts as too risk to treat conservatively with risk of rupture. O elects pts, consent form signed. Cannula placed RF and pentoject given iv, passed away peacefully. O elects to bury at home.
"hr 208 no weight loss.  small area dermatitis medial canthus. .  monitior for now. discussed y/d diet."

"client claiming for treatment therefore is finding out how much excess is and bringing in form... Has FORL on 208 (upper L carnassial), advise dental removal. owner may want pabs due to previous kidney probs. advise of price. to pay"

Owner reports <<name>> has been going downhill in the last several months and after monitoring her over the easter break she realized he is really uncomfortable so she decided to call it a day for her today. Had to sedate, placed intravenous cathether, 5 ml pentoject used. Owner would appreciated a paw print and a clip of <<location>> and will collect her body in 1-2 days. also will like to pay over the phone.

HISTORY=had dental with multiple extractions in 6th of Jan, O agreeed for dental then as <<identifier>> was in a lot of pain. This morning O noticved that she started with the same signs, sharp pain and then she's yelping. very painful when owner is opening her mouth, and also not been eating well at all for the last 24h. CLINICAL EXAMINATION= QAR in the consult, mouthlooks fine, heald very well, suspect pain is more neurological, reluctent to move her head left/right, up/down. O prefer to PTS her, as not able to afford future investigations. convinced O to try symptomatic treatmetn for now. also advise if she's doing well can have a written prescription next time. DIFFERENTIAL DIAGNOSIS=cervical spinal pain.  PLAN: analgesia and to re-examine if not any better. O ok with the plan. ESTIMATE PROVIDED (Y/N): DISCUSSED COSTS (Y/N): RECHECK (Y/N + WHEN?):
"a311b01 trio. 49j601 felv. fine no problems."
"sympathy card sent"

"Hm- body sent for private cremation and sympathy card sent. carrier out back labelled. Collar by reception - owner very upset so unsure if wants.  EM -TJ is attacking dogs in the <<identifier>> ! and just sitting in the middle of <<location>> even when cars come , and walking very close to the owners so that they amost trip, and sometimes he lashes out at them. I suspect he may be hyperthyroid plus/minus some senility. <<name>> has diabetes and they are worried about skin infections if she gets scratched, so opted for euthanasia, and hes getting individual cremation scatter tube."

sadly, owner think her qol has declined in last few days they think she might be in pain now, and yesterday was having trouble chewing food. went peacefully, offered condolences. please keep on hold for now, owner will call back on monday to decided if would like indiv crem with scatter tube, please price on accordingly when owner decides
"right flank.  burst lump /cyst , squeezed content out if not resolving then excise."

"History:2 year old rat with severe neurological signs. porphyrin staining at eyes and over whishers and fore legs. Clinical Exam: unable to stand p[roperly. Differential Diagnosis: brain tumour?? Plan: adv PTS."
<<name>>. old age.lots weight loss. went v peacefully

"Presented due to ongoing anorexia and drooling. mass ventral mandible has increased in size, especially left side. seems to have grown medially also. hard on palpation. advised owner suspect this is tumour. advised prognosis is guarded. palliative care is really the only option as doubtful surgery is possible and if it is it would be very invasive, and given age don't think this is best option for him. dispensed pred/antirobe in case of infection. gave owner information on cremation options. also injected 0.3ml vetergesic i/m in case pain is reason why he's not eating. advised can dispense more vetergesic if he is more inclined to eat when this is on board. o to keep us updated with progress."
"generally bright and well, abdo palp NAD ,chest sounds are clear, HR 120 sounding fine - discuss dental scale and polish and poss extraction advised within next 12-18m."
Owner arrived at surgery without apt, dog unable to walk and very laboured breathing. Sympathy card sent. Reminders removed

"in for 6 month health check. owner reports no problems. skin and coat lovely. ears clean, no inflammation or hairs. no discharge from eyes or nose. teeth really good for her age, some tartar on canine all other fine no inflammation or reddness of gums. eating, drinking toileting as nrmal. exercis fine is giveing a oint supplement as getting older but still wants to go for walkd as normal"
"last season end jan off colour suspect pyo on abdomen palpation.  scan confirms. no vulval discharge.  admirt to spey. o declined bloods."
"responded well to ronaxan tabes but recurrence of R nasal discharge o doesnt want further investigations, advise 3wk course ronaxan -oredered as non in stock o to ring Mon to check arrived."
v mis. dehydrated. resp inc. ascites. lump noted before is bigger and knobbly ?liver. advise o nothing to be done, other than pts. arr for later at <<location>>.

"Hx: o reports gunky eyes, greeny colour discharge, no pain / squinting, otherwise happy and healthy dog. Ce: at the medial canthus of both eyes, borwny green mucoid discharge, -ve stain uptake, schirmmer tear test >15mm in 1min, no signs of uveitis, cornea looks nice and clear, mild inflammation of the conjunctiva. Plan: fucithalmic BID, rv INB in 5 days."

"anal sacs. eag +++ r>l no infection but v full again had a little cry with the right one so try recheck in 8 weeks may be able to gradually increase time inbetween, glands are quite deep. Next appointment in 8 weeks."

Investigations and PTS. O reports is non weightbearing LF now. Fell out of owners arms twice over weekend and lameness has got worse since these occasions. Still drinking, urinating, defeacating, eating. Breathing bad still - dex and torb made no improvement. Lf- signif swelling just distal to carpus. Non weightbearing lame. Breathing horrific as per Friday. Tongue slightly blue tinged. O did not want to PTS this morning. Keen to investigate. Adv can xray foot, suspect underlying fracture, but also to investig chest further again whilst under GA. Adv high risks of GA. os elected DNR if arrests. Routine GA. - premed <<name>> IV. - coinduced with diazepam and propofol slow iv to effect. - maintained on iso in o2 via et tube. RL, LL and DV peak insp thoracic rads: Elevation of trachea. Enlargement to cardiac silhouette, tenting of left atrium, increased sternal contact. Bronchio-interstitial pattern caudodorsal lungfields. LA:Ao ratio 1.7 average.  Fracture to digit 5 LF. Oblique full thickness fracture through proximal metacarpal next to MCP joint. Adv O concurrent issues - fracture and evidence of CHF. Adv PTS kindest given extent of resp difficulties when conscious. O gave verbal consent to both HP and TS over phone. To collect to take to <<location>> crem. IV pento, death confirmed by lack of heartbeat

"No problems reported by owner - in for anual vac. BAR quiet and easy to examine. h - 160, r - 40. ce wnl. D/G 2.5/5 - minimal tartar build up. appropriate candidate for vac. ducat/felv a023a02/5d1h01."

Owner brought in for PTS, worried not going to cope indoors and worried re pup, Is walking a lot better, still very wonky LH but weight bearing and comfortable. bright and fussy. advise give the cat a try, has been with brother. may find copes at home better than thinks will do.

"o reports much improved not shaking head now. ears nothing abnormal detected now apart from some wax right ear, allowed to clean in prep. o wishes to have checked regular and clean as necessary as cant do at home. advise rv 2 weeks check and can clean if necessary. can put cleaner on file and o can bring with to subsequent appointments. Next appointment in 2 weeks."

"check up for repeat metacam. doing well generally. fine in himself. is having days now where he is increasingly stiff. bright in himself. is getting a little more exercise than usual, owner making sure not to overdo it with exercise. nothing abnormal detected on general exam. very wriggly when come to legs and wont cooperate for exam of legs. no particular lameness. does bunny hop a little when moves quickly in here. advised metacam for as required. can collect metacam for 6months from now."
"Booster l A211a02 and KC A054B01"
"booster. no examination as not keen on being handled. given injection im as wouldnt tollerate being touched too much to tent skin for subcut injection."

check over. <<name>> and friend <<name>> brought in, started sunday with diarrhea, came down monday morning and three more lots; also not wanting to eat; subdued, vomiting as well. both <<name>> and <<name>> denied any knowledge of previous concerns with liver values - but <<name>> aware of Cushings disease. pe - LARGE abdominal mass - can't get hand around it at all; h\l - 90bpm. kindest option euthanasia. both <<name>> and <<name>> quite upset - breiefly mentioned\discussed investigations but age against <<name>>. <<name>> enquiring if it is <<name>>'s stomach - advised that mass is in the mid-cranial abdomen - could be spleen, liver, stomch, intestines, adrenal gland, kidney, other. declined euth today - wanted to take home; advised and discussed that don't want <<name>> to suffer\be in pain. scheduled for end of morning surgery - hopefully 12pm for house visit - o aware of cost for this; will be using pets@rest for cremation

"Sedation + Abdo US. dom/torb, reversed with atp.  large extra and intra-hepatic liver shunts - tuburlent blood flow. 1.95cmx1.95cm mesenteric mass within caudal abdomen. thickened gut wall.  likely multi-centric lymphoma. advised PTS."
"? sight smell reducing reduced retinal vessels suspect pra is fine at home leave as is problem will come with unfamiliar surrounding no evidence hypertension or retinal detachment."

Abdo mass on scan. Now d+, gone downhill over night. Abdo disntedned and uncomfy to aplp. Prognosis guarded and now unable to take meloxiad for joints. Felt put to sleep kidnest option, this was performmed with Mooch going back to YCR for burial.

"deteriorated - possible pts. not eating/drinking or defecated, urinating. at home he has been laying flat, walks for a little bit and then lays down.  dyspnoeic in basket, white mucous membranes, gasping for breath, unable to take weight on hindlimbs, abdomen very large and fluid filled.  Discussed and recommended put to sleep as he looks like he is on his way out. other option would be to stay in with o2 supplementation, abdominal drainage, further steroids and pain relief. however this wont give him much more time or QOL. owner decided to put to sleep, signed form and going for communial cremation. owners wanted to stay with him throughout and therefore i attempted to place an IV catheter in the consult room. There was no venous access and little pulse. He was starting to gasp and spasm so i asked the owner if we could bring him to the back room to gas him down and put to sleep there. owner agreed. Think he passed on his own, but injected pentoject intracardiac. confirmed deceased."
signs of brain tumour.  head tilt etc so await owners decission on euth

Status Epilepticus. OR discovered at home tremoring, tried to bite owner and fitting continously. Hyperthermic (39.1).  HR =200, pulses normal.  panting.  extended head and neck.  Given 4mL intravenous diazepam, no effect.  Give another 4mL intravenous diazepam 10 mins later.  Induced with 18ml of propofol. Reduced temperature to 38.5 and heart rate 84.  Unstable recovery - no response or consciousness.  Discussed guarded prognosis and PTS.

Booked in for PTS but O decided not right time. Had long discussion with O about right time to PTS. O will have a thik over the next couple of days. OR has been v+ about once a day. Asked if there's anything we can give for nausea. Offered prevomax inj but advised no oral form for cats.
"Discuss with owner renal failure, prostatic mass, lost alot of weight, not eating, vomiting, need to consoder QOL & advise euthanasia."
"Worse. Trying to circle R now. Think O will have euthanasia later today."

EUTH.  peaceful euth with o present. tried to placed IVC <<name>> B conscious but went to bite. so gave 2 mg/kg alfax and 0.4 mg/kg butorphanol IM. sedation very effective. placed IVC with o present. gave 30 ml pentoject IV. confirmed asystole and no corneal reflex.  o req <<identifier>> with casket

PE: QAR, mucous membranes p+m, crt <2s, hr160bpm, nothing abnormal detected on abdo palpation, T38.5. advised bloods to investigate weight loss, alternatively try symptomatic treatment initially. owner requested euthanasia. advised against as may be treatable, owner would still prefer euthanasia."

"Booster + heart murmur not noted before. Hx - doing fine at home, no problems reported. DUDE, no V/D/C/S. eyes doing fine, currently 1 drop optimmune SID. PE - eyes - no discharge/inflammtion/blephrospasm. slight ectropian (breed?). ears, nose, oral exam NAD. abdo palp NAD. entire - testicles same size, no pain, regualr. cardiac - grade 2 murmur, LHS - not noted prev - exercise tolerence unchanged, no tachycardia no coughing, Rest RR unchanged as far as O aware. lung ausc NAD. discussed heart disease investigations (though no CS at present) - O keen. start with pro-BNP and then possible thoracic x-ray + BP + baseline cbc/bio if warrented. will ring O with results and discuss plan. Gave vacc + KC. also dispensed written prescription for optimmune - 6 months."

"check eyes much better and dont appear to vbe rolling in now so leave"

Owners report QoL deteriorated. discussed investigaiton options would be looking at bloods/scans/x-rays. owners don't want to over investigate have decided on euthansia. sedated dom/torb i/m good response. passed away peacefully, communal cremation

Discussed with owner referral to a STS. Discussed lengthy healing process of open wounds. Tme effort and money and <<location>> wellbeing. O's have opt for euth."

"recheck. possible improved a littel over weekend. started to eat a bit more but then vomited back up again. almost immediately. no vomit since sunday. not interesetd at all today in food. no D+ but not really passed much. urinating ok. drinking +++. on exam mm pink in conjunctiva - can not see mm in mouth due to muzzle. HR 180 and difficult to hear clearly. cannot tell if murmur. dyspnoea ++. abdo palp ok. temperature reduced to 38.7c - better. concern re dysnoea and pupd. advise scan chest for pleural fluid and bloods. concern re cost as owner pensioner. scan reveals 2cm pocket pleural fluid on R but lung in way, less on L but large amount lung. will be difficult to drain due to dog temperament (require sedation) and access not easy. heart appears to be contracting well and no obvious HCM. discussed trial frusemide and assess respinse 48 hours. ini on scan then sedate to drain?? full chest scan and heart assessment. advise also re bloods to axiom for PUPD to check underlying cause. owner agreed. sample of pleural fluid stored for now due t cost. advise owner i am not here - will be different vet."

PC Anorexia, weakness; Comp/haem/lytes; Euthanasia & Individual Cremation & casket. returned from <<identifier>> Monday (with view to CCL surgery). Hyporexia last few days but now anorexia. Refused even bacon, cheese whch is unheard of. Very week. Needs assistance to get up. Started pred 18/2/19. Started Chlorambucil, Omeprazole, Pardale, Plavix 20/2/19. O has managed to get all of these in. No vomiting. No faeces today. Yesterday passed very dark, possibly black diarrhoea. Exam. Very pale. Marked ascites. O reports not clearly any worse. HR 136 & regular. Weak synchronous pulse with varying intensity. T 38.9. Concerns include anaemia, hypovolaemia, hyponatremia as well as the ongoing hypoproteinaemia. Guarded to poor outlook. Discussed & opted to run bloods then decide between options of PTS, treatment here, refer to AMVS for ICU. LAB. Albumin slightly increased (19). Urea 16.3H + - possible GI blood related. Na 142N, K 5.7h+, Na/K 24.91. Probably not HoAC. No longer hyponatremia. WBC 42.4h++, Neuts 36. RBC 2.49L+, HCT 16.9l+. Haemorrhage appears likliest. Perhaps all GI related but may be further cause of bleed. Discussed referral for transfusions & further investigation but given guarded outlook, opted to PTS. Euthanasia & individual cremation & traditional casket - O aware may need to break casket to scatter ashes at later date. Lab Request References Generated: Comprehensive Panel is 016240. Electrolytes Profile is 016240. Haematology (4 Part) is 016240. please could we inform HPC that <<identifier>> RIP

Sore past few days left hind -was very sore now improved weight bearing but tentative.  e/d/u/d normally. LH -nails/ pads ok, toes ok, no obvious fx, slight restriction flex/ extension, no obvious pain reaction. rec rest and nsaid 1 week see back ini.

<<name>> Client reports remains PUPD, reports abdomen sometimes appears swollen, but not so much today. Plan: abdo u/s (previous splenic mass and renal changes) and biochem& SDMA. Abdominal ultrasound: No free peritoneal fluid. The splenic mass appears exactly the same size as previous examination (3.8cm diamater, previously 3.7-3.8cm). Remaining spleen and liver nad, small amount of sediment in GB, but otherwise nad. Both renal cortices remain slightly hyperechoeic, as before, no pyelectasia, stones or cysts.  Assessment: No change in splenic mass - malignant lesion less likely. On balance, I dont think we should rush in a splenectomise this dog (ht murmur, 12yrs old). Renal changes similar to before.  UREA & crea ok, ALKP elevated slightly.  Discussed with O - no change in splenic mass, malignancy less likely, but cannot rule out. Adv rescan in 3 months. The cause of the PUPD cannot definitively be determined today, but we suspect renal disease (based on ultrasound findings) - adv sdma is much more sensitive marker of early renal disease than urea/crea. Plan: No need for any meds at this stage. adv continue as we are, monitoring, and await SDMA. Discuss with <<identifier>>."

Mars has been doing well last couple of days, beginning to get out more and eating well, RR still sitting between 28-32 so is still up a little but effort looks less, still having occasional wretching type episodes approx once daily. Bloods taken to check electrolytes and kidney parameters on frusemide as was previously a little hypokalaemic. Fluid analysis was consistent with a Modified transudate which can occur associated with many different causes including cardiovascular disease, hypertension, infectious, haemorrhage, glomerulonephritis, and neoplasia or conditions causing impaired lymphatic drainage such as neoplasia or granulomatous inflammation etc so quite non specific.  Discussed plan with O going forward, v much about QOL, could CT chest etc but unlikely to change management, o would not want chemotherapy etc if tumour was found. Plan to keep on low dose of frusemide and may add in clopidogrel and K supps if needed. O aware condition likely progressive but QOL good at present so for now will monitor RR and see how gets on with meds.
